10 VIVA QUESTIONS

1.	What is the purpose of the RS (Register Select) pin in an LCD?
2.	Explain the difference between Command Mode and Data Mode in an LCD.
3.	Why is delay() necessary when sending commands to an LCD?
4.	What is "Debouncing" in the context of sensors, and why is the delay(50) added in the loop?
5.	What happens to the object_detected flag if the IR sensor is permanently blocked?
6.	Explain the logic of IO1PIN = cmd << 16;. Why is the bit-shift necessary?
7.	What is the role of PINSEL registers in the LPC2148?
8.	How does the system distinguish between a new object and the same object remaining in front of the sensor?
9.	What is the significance of the command array values (e.g., 0x38, 0x01)?
10.	If you wanted to interface an ultrasonic sensor instead of an IR sensor for this project, what major changes would be required in the code?

